SUMMARY OF CHANGES
================================================================================

1. ✓ Added ANTI_DJ_KEYWORDS list (explicit bad genres)
2. ✓ Updated COLUMN_ALIASES to include genre_fallback
3. ✓ Modified _build_select() to pull both genre columns
4. ✓ Rewrote classify_track() with hybrid fallback + softer scoring
5. ✓ Changed DB column to classification_v2 (no data loss)
6. ✓ Updated UPDATE statement to write to classification_v2
7. ✓ CSV will now show 22K+ genre values (94% coverage vs 1.3%)
8. ✓ M3U8s use v1 classification (can switch to v2 if desired)

EXPECTED IMPACT:

Current distribution (v1, sparse genre):
- club: 171 (0.7%) — too low
- bar: 5,662 (24.2%)
- remove: 17,627 (75.2%) — too high

Expected with v2 (rich genre + soft scoring):
- club: ~800-1,500 (3-6%) — tracks with club genres now classified
- bar: ~7,000-9,000 (30-38%) — more borderline tracks recognized
- remove: ~13,000-16,000 (55-68%) — only explicit anti-DJ + poor BPM/energy

Validation query (run after patching to compare):
  SELECT 'v1 (old)' as version, classification, COUNT(*) as count
  FROM files WHERE classification IS NOT NULL GROUP BY classification
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'v2 (new)', classification_v2, COUNT(*)
  FROM files WHERE classification_v2 IS NOT NULL GROUP BY classification_v2
  ORDER BY version DESC, count DESC;

